<tr><td bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>
<center><strong>Charm</strong></center>
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<table width=70%>
<tr><td>Mana:</td>
<td>60</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill:</td>
<td>Alteration</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>
Classes:</td>
<td>
<a href="/spells/enchanter.shtml">
Enchanter</a>
 (12)<BR>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Buyable:</td><td>
Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Researchable:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drops from MOB:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cast Time:</td>
<td>2.40 seconds</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><br></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>Description:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
Effect of charm.<BR>
<BR>
Duration is (Level * 3) + 10 ticks.</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<BR>1 tick = 6 seconds<BR>
When a range of effects are given, it usually means that the effect becomes more potent as the caster increases in levels.
</td></tr>
