<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: aabumen</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-23 12:13:48</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Don't do this solo until you get high charisma.<BR>
<BR>
High charisma effects the NPCs 'saving roll' to resist and to break out of Charm (duration).<BR>
<BR>
Prior to 120+ Charisma you will really, really not appreciate the use of the spell. Sure it will work out cool once in a while, but trust me, suffering is awaiting you.<BR>
<BR>
Do in group that can save your hide when the baddie gets rather pissed at you. Expect 1 second duration. Be elated when it lasts longer (hey, it's random, it can happen =)<BR>
<BR>
Now. you've done some gnarley Enchanter quests. And you have your Charisma buffs. And you bought your stinkin twinked Enchanter some CHA jewelry. Cool. 150+ Charisma is where this REALLY starts to shine and define your class. Now get your Enchanted hide down to sol b and charm a Greater Kobold and impress all the ladies. And their tanky beaus =) Seriously, my Beguile either lasts a few seconds (gotta keep it random, don't we Verant =(  ), or lasts the full duration of 8 minutes. Trust me. Animations suck. You just don't know it until you see a real mob whacking out the dmg. Absolutely embarrases even the best tanks when it comes to dmg. Or go do Spectres in Oasis with Charm (they were yellow when I first tried this. It worked very well - MOST of the time =)<BR>
<BR>
FYI I LOVE playing my enchanter. But my first 'high' came when I blurred something and saved someone's hide. That was level 4. MUCH later the 2nd high came when I charmed a spec. Floored my group mates =) I got some serious respect.<BR>
<BR>
Still safer in groups, but doable solo near zone line or other safety when you got high CHA.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
