<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ranany  (The Rathe)</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-23 19:53:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white><BR>
<BR>
Well Charming is good but I only do it at the begining of the fight..... then I sit and med up... How else do you think I solo the Spectre Isle and still have a bubble of mana at 42?  Sure I lose ONE Spectre for exp but i make up for it in the long run. My charisma is only 130 (NOTE:  I havent done the indacesent mask or gloves quest yet and do not have the +9 charisma braclets) If you are soloing and you decide to use charm be sure to make sure the thing isnt too powerful... or make sure it almost dies or is very weak. When charm goes off he will be VERY made at you and if he has full hps and u not then you might be in trouble.<BR>
What I do is tell the pet to sit then run off invis then quickly root the MoB and eith there <BR>
<BR>
1) Memory Blur it or<BR>
2) Finish it off<BR>
<BR>
Just some ideas and what not also to disprove what Aabumen said.. You DO need high charisma as an Enchanter but with under 150 is okay.... <BR>
